n a rotation you must:<br>
<br>
a) Be able to kill the mob being rotated. This means that if you have not already killed it, you must be able to assemble the force and take it down before another guild. If Sev is to be rotated and a guild not currently on the rotation decides to try him and begins to gather the forces first (say 20-30 ppl to start), they should be given attempts at him without the interference of the guild currently up in the rotation.<br>
<br>
b) The guild must be able to kill the mob which is to be rotated without the assistance of another guild (1 group being acceptable maybe?). If guilds form alliances to take down such mobs, then they will be placed on the rotation as one allied entity.<br>
<br>
These are the basis for many of the current rotations on the server and I'm not sure if the guilds you added to the proposed rotation in your post meet this criteria.<br>
<br>
Trakanon and Severilous are two very different dragons. Trak is considered the easier dragon of Kunark with the exception of Faydedar. A guild capable of killing Trakanon cannot necessarily kill Severilous, due to his fear, (which Trak does not have) and his AE stun.<br>
<br>
The following is not set in stone, but I believe Tindi and Noble Blade will not be interested in Severilous in the near future due to the fact that both guilds have small demand for many warrior epics.<br>
<br>
<br>
Tibben Thunderfoot<br>
60 Hierophant<br>
